THE family of the late media personality Kuli Roberts have shared details of her funeral and memorial service. According to the statement shared by the family, Kuli will be laid to rest on Thursday, 17 February and her memorial service will be held the day before at Birchwood Hotel. “The funeral of the beloved public figure Nomakula ‘Kuli’ Roberts will take place at a private ceremony in Joburg and the service will be live-streamed," the statement reads. ALSO READ | BLUE MBOMBO REVEALS PREGANANCY "Both the Roberts and the Mboya family are deeply thankful for the immense support from across the nation in the past few days and have planned a small intimate gathering for her send-off. Invited close friends and media will gather for a special memorial in celebration of the life of Nomakula ‘Kuli’ Roberts this Wednesday and the memorial service will be streamed lived." The well-decorated media personality and author passed away on Wednesday, 9 February after she complained of shortness of breath and collapsed. Since then messages of condolences have been pouring in for her with many saying they will miss her humour. pic.twitter.com/SM1TEBJd1K 